      "Missing bilious (green) vomiting as a red flag for obstruction in any child",
      "Not recognizing lethargy between episodes as a worrisome sign (altered mentation from ischemia or shock)",
      "Ordering CT instead of ultrasound (US is more sensitive and avoids radiation in children)",
      "Delaying surgical consultation while awaiting enema \u2014 surgeon should be aware in case reduction fails",
      "Discharging after successful enema reduction without observation \u2014 recurrence rate 5-10% within 72 hours"
