          "teaching": "\u2705 Key teaching: ACE-I angioedema is BRADYKININ-mediated, not histamine. Antihistamines and steroids don't work. Discontinue ACE-I permanently. Avoid ARBs. Document allergy. Switch to amlodipine or other non-RAAS antihypertensive. Observe 24-48h."
