    "keyLearningPoints": [
      "Eclampsia = preeclampsia + seizures. It can occur antepartum, intrapartum, or postpartum (up to 6 weeks after delivery)",
      "MAGNESIUM SULFATE is the treatment of choice for seizure prevention AND treatment in eclampsia \u2014 4-6g IV loading dose, then 1-2g/hr drip",
      "Definitive treatment is DELIVERY OF THE BABY AND PLACENTA \u2014 the placenta is the source of the disease",
      "HELLP syndrome (Hemolysis, Elevated Liver enzymes, Low Platelets) is a severe complication \u2014 this patient has it",
      "Blood pressure management: IV labetalol or hydralazine, target SBP <160 and DBP <110 to prevent stroke",
      "Magnesium toxicity monitoring: check reflexes (loss = first sign of toxicity), respiratory rate, and serum Mg levels"
    ],
    "mustNotMiss": [
      "HELLP syndrome (platelets <100, elevated LFTs, hemolysis \u2014 can cause liver rupture, DIC, maternal death)",
      "Placental abruption (vaginal bleeding, painful uterus, fetal distress \u2014 common with severe preeclampsia)",
      "Posterior Reversible Encephalopathy Syndrome (PRES) \u2014 can progress to permanent injury if BP not controlled",
      "DIC (falling fibrinogen, prolonged PT, bleeding \u2014 trigger massive transfusion protocol if needed)",
      "Hepatic rupture/subcapsular hematoma (RUQ pain + hemodynamic instability = catastrophic)",
      "Intracranial hemorrhage (most common cause of maternal death in eclampsia)"
    ],
    "commonPitfalls": [
      "Using phenytoin or benzodiazepines instead of magnesium \u2014 magnesium is superior for eclamptic seizures",
      "Not starting magnesium until seizure occurs \u2014 should be started for severe preeclampsia prophylactically",
      "Not delivering the baby \u2014 the only cure is delivery, even if preterm",
      "Treating elevated BP too aggressively (sudden drops can compromise uteroplacental flow \u2014 gradual reduction)",
      "Missing HELLP in a patient with 'just preeclampsia' \u2014 always check CBC, LFTs, LDH",
      "Attributing eclamptic seizure to epilepsy without checking preeclampsia labs",
      "Not monitoring for magnesium toxicity (therapeutic range narrow: 4-7 mEq/L, >10 = respiratory arrest)"
    ],
