      "NMS tetrad: Fever + Rigidity (lead-pipe) + Altered Mental Status + Autonomic Instability (tachycardia, BP lability, diaphoresis)",
      "STOP the causative antipsychotic IMMEDIATELY \u2014 this is the most important step",
      "CK is typically markedly elevated (>1,000, often >10,000) from rhabdomyolysis",
      "Treatment: aggressive IV fluids (target UOP 200-300mL/hr), cooling measures, dantrolene (muscle relaxant) and/or bromocriptine (dopamine agonist)",
      "NMS develops over DAYS (unlike serotonin syndrome which develops over HOURS) \u2014 key timeline distinguisher",
      "ICU admission required \u2014 mortality is 10-20% even with treatment; complications include AKI, DIC, respiratory failure"
