    "keyLearningPoints": [
      "Thyroid storm is diagnosed CLINICALLY using the Burch-Wartofsky Score (>45 = thyroid storm): fever, tachycardia, CNS dysfunction, GI symptoms, CHF, precipitant",
      "Treatment order matters: (1) Beta-blocker (propranolol \u2014 also blocks T4\u2192T3 conversion), (2) Thionamide (PTU preferred in storm \u2014 blocks new synthesis AND T4\u2192T3 conversion), (3) Iodine (SSKI \u2014 blocks hormone RELEASE, must give 1 hour AFTER thionamide), (4) Steroids (hydrocortisone \u2014 blocks T4\u2192T3 conversion and treats possible relative adrenal insufficiency), (5) Cooling measures",
      "This patient is PTU-allergic (hepatotoxicity) \u2014 use methimazole + propranolol + iodine + steroids",
      "AFib in thyroid storm: rate control with beta-blocker first; cardioversion often fails until euthyroid",
      "Mortality of untreated thyroid storm is >90%; even with treatment, mortality is 10-30%",
      "Identify and treat the precipitant \u2014 in this case: medication non-compliance + dental procedure stress"
    ],
    "mustNotMiss": [
      "Sepsis (fever + tachycardia + altered mental status \u2014 overlapping features; infection can also trigger thyroid storm)",
      "Cocaine/sympathomimetic intoxication (agitation, tachycardia, hypertension \u2014 check UDS)",
      "Pheochromocytoma crisis (paroxysmal HTN, tachycardia, diaphoresis \u2014 but no goiter or eye findings)",
      "Serotonin syndrome (agitation, tachycardia, hyperthermia \u2014 but would have clonus and serotonergic drug)",
      "Malignant hyperthermia / NMS (rigidity, hyperthermia \u2014 different exam findings)"
    ],
    "commonPitfalls": [
      "Giving iodine BEFORE thionamide \u2014 iodine provides substrate for MORE hormone synthesis if production isn't blocked first",
      "Using only beta-blockers without thionamide and iodine \u2014 beta-blockers treat symptoms but don't stop the hormone storm",
      "Not giving stress-dose steroids \u2014 relative adrenal insufficiency is common and steroids also block T4\u2192T3 conversion",
      "Cardioverting AFib before achieving rate control and starting antithyroid therapy \u2014 will likely recur",
      "Not checking for precipitating infection \u2014 dental extraction site, UTI, pneumonia can all trigger storm",
      "Sending patient to a general ward \u2014 thyroid storm requires ICU monitoring"
    ],
