    "keyLearningPoints": [
      "Adrenal crisis = hypotension refractory to IV fluids + known or suspected adrenal insufficiency \u2192 GIVE STRESS-DOSE STEROIDS IMMEDIATELY",
      "Treatment: IV hydrocortisone 100mg STAT bolus, then 50mg IV every 8 hours. At stress doses, hydrocortisone provides adequate mineralocorticoid activity \u2014 fludrocortisone not needed acutely",
      "Adrenal crisis triad: hypotension + hyponatremia + hyperkalemia (with hypoglycemia and eosinophilia)",
      "DO NOT wait for cortisol results before treating \u2014 clinical diagnosis, give steroids first",
      "Precipitants: medication non-compliance, intercurrent illness without stress-dosing, surgery, trauma, adrenal hemorrhage",
      "Hyperpigmentation (skin + mucosal) = PRIMARY adrenal insufficiency (high ACTH stimulates melanocytes). Secondary (pituitary) has no hyperpigmentation."
    ],
    "mustNotMiss": [
      "Hyperkalemia with ECG changes (peaked T waves, widened QRS \u2014 treat with calcium gluconate, insulin/D50, kayexalate before cardiac arrest)",
      "Hypoglycemia (check point-of-care glucose immediately \u2014 give D50W)",
      "Sepsis (overlapping features: hypotension, AMS, tachycardia \u2014 must rule out concurrent infection as precipitant)",
      "Myxedema coma (hypothyroidism component \u2014 if concurrent with adrenal crisis, treat adrenal insufficiency FIRST before thyroid hormone)",
      "Bilateral adrenal hemorrhage (Waterhouse-Friderichsen syndrome in meningococcal sepsis \u2014 DIC + adrenal crisis)"
    ],
    "commonPitfalls": [
      "Not recognizing adrenal crisis because hypotension is attributed to 'dehydration' or 'sepsis' and doesn't respond to fluids alone",
      "Waiting for cortisol level before giving steroids \u2014 this is a medical emergency, treat empirically",
      "Not treating hyperkalemia urgently \u2014 K+ 6.4 with ECG changes can cause fatal arrhythmia",
      "Forgetting to check and treat hypoglycemia \u2014 cortisol-deficient patients cannot maintain blood sugar",
      "Ordering cosyntropin stimulation test in acute crisis \u2014 this delays treatment and is unreliable in acute setting",
      "Not educating patient on stress-dosing and providing emergency injection kit at discharge"
    ],
