    "keyLearningPoints": [
      "TTP classic pentad: thrombocytopenia + MAHA (schistocytes) + neurologic symptoms + renal dysfunction + fever \u2014 but full pentad present in <5% of cases. DO NOT wait for all five.",
      "PLASTT score for TTP probability: Platelet count, Lysis markers (LDH, reticulocytes, indirect bilirubin), ADAMTS13 activity, Smear (schistocytes), Two differentials (normal coags rules out DIC)",
      "TREATMENT = PLASMA EXCHANGE (plasmapheresis) \u2014 removes anti-ADAMTS13 antibodies and replaces ADAMTS13. Must be started EMERGENTLY \u2014 mortality >90% without treatment, <20% with treatment.",
      "ADAMTS13 activity <10% confirms TTP \u2014 but DO NOT wait for result before starting plasma exchange (takes days to return). Send and treat empirically.",
      "DO NOT TRANSFUSE PLATELETS \u2014 adding platelets to the microvascular thrombi is 'adding fuel to the fire' and can precipitate stroke/MI. Only transfuse for life-threatening hemorrhage.",
      "Normal PT/INR and fibrinogen DISTINGUISH TTP from DIC \u2014 in DIC, the coagulation cascade is activated and fibrinogen is consumed."
    ],
