      "DIC is ALWAYS secondary to an underlying cause \u2014 treat the cause (in this case: surgical hemostasis + massive transfusion for hemorrhagic shock)",
      "THE LETHAL TRIAD: Hypothermia + Acidosis + Coagulopathy \u2014 each worsens the others in a death spiral. Must address ALL THREE simultaneously.",
      "MASSIVE TRANSFUSION PROTOCOL (MTP): balanced ratio of pRBC:FFP:platelets at 1:1:1. Most hospitals have MTP activation \u2014 use it.",
      "DIC labs: prolonged PT/INR + prolonged PTT + LOW fibrinogen + ELEVATED D-dimer + thrombocytopenia + schistocytes. This distinguishes DIC from TTP (TTP has normal coags/fibrinogen).",
