          "aiPatientUpdate": null,
          "teaching": "\u2705 Overcorrection causes osmotic demyelination syndrome (ODS) \u2014 devastating pontine and extrapontine damage. If Na rises too fast: DDAVP clamp + D5W to lower back. Correct underlying cause: stop SSRI, stop HCTZ. Long-term SIADH management: fluid restriction, tolvaptan, or urea."
