          "ecg": "NSR",
          "labHighlights": {},
          "examNote": "Hives improving. Pruritus better. No anaphylaxis features. Likely post-viral urticaria.",
          "aiPatientUpdate": "The hives are fading and the itching is so much better.",
          "teaching": "Acute urticaria: self-limited in 80%+. Individual wheals<24h (if>24h, consider urticarial vasculitis-biopsy). Most common triggers: viral, drugs, foods. Treatment: H1 antihistamine. Discharge: continue cetirizine scheduled (not PRN) x2 weeks. Return if respiratory symptoms develop."
